The{road system}follows ancient tracks and paths. These are found along the valley bottoms and along the ridges of the hills. They are connected by roads which are often narrow and zigzagging. It is somewhat perturbing to be able to see one's destination from the ridge yet have to travel a considerable way by road to reach it. The area is crisscrossed by footpaths, many surviving from ancient times.
During heavy snowfall in{winter} travel is only possible by road and can be extremely difficult. All the most important roads are kept open by constant gritting.{
It is usual to find the roads being used by herds of{cows}which are travelling between fields and milking parlours.
